UDP data toss!!

1. Program options

data_toss -p <Port> -i <IP address> -t <number of threads> -d -q -s

Default values:
Port: 9930
IP Address: 127.0.0.1 (localhost)
Number of threads: 5
Daemon Mode: False
Quiet Mode: False
Seamless Mode: False --> Toss out garbages without showing anywhing... endlessly...


2. Compile options (Makefile options)
default: gcc debug compilation. Slow as hell.
release: gcc release.
pgi: uses PGI compiler.
mpi: Not fully implemented yet. MPICH.
llvm: uses clang (make sure you have it) compiler.
clean: yeap, clean everything up.
